{
  "texts": [
    "An Autoencoder (AE) is an unsupervised Artificial Neural Network (ANN) designed to replicate its input at its output (Al-Garadi et al. 2020).",
    "It consists of two main components: an encoder and a decoder.",
    "Each component includes one or more hidden layers.",
    "The encoder takes the input and transforms it into a feature-based representation, thereby reducing the dimensionality of the data.",
    "The decoder then attempts to reconstruct the original input from this representation."
  ]
}